The notation "∫" is used in other parts of mathlib. The following should make "open Pseudofunctor.Grothendieck" necessary to get this notation:
```suggestion
namespace Pseudofunctor.Grothendieck

scoped prefix:75 "∫ " => Pseudofunctor.Grothendieck
```
Thanks!! I'm somewhat new to defining notation :)

This should be fine if you adding `variable (F)` before the declaration:
```suggestion
def forget : ∫ F ⥤ 𝒮 where
```
You should add a bibtex format entry in the file `docs/references.bib`.

```suggestion
  obj X := X.base
  map f := f.base
```

```suggestion
    · simp [F.mapComp_id_right_inv_app, Strict.rightUnitor_eqToIso, ← NatTrans.naturality_assoc]
```

```suggestion
    · simp [← NatTrans.naturality_assoc, F.mapComp_assoc_right_inv_app,
        Strict.associator_eqToIso]
```
